Defendant Larry Bishop in court with attorney Hazel Jean Washington.  Nathaniel Emery Adamson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.  The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 3 days time served.  Huber privileges for Work/AODA/Child care pursuant to Sec. 303.08 Wis. Stats to apply.  Court ordered defendant pay costs and victim/witness surcharges by 1/15/2017; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment.  Court ordered defendant provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharges by 1/15/2017; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment.  Court is NOT suspending defendant's drivers license.  Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon he may no longer use or possess any firearms or body armor; also he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been restored.
